        </param>
        <param>
          <type>TickType_t</type>
          <declname>delay_ticks</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Receives a FDCAN message. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Reads a message from the receive queue corresponding to the specified ID. Supports blocking or non-blocking behavior depending on delay_ticks.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>handle</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the FDCAN handle structure. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>id</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>CAN identifier of the message to receive. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>header</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to a FDCAN_RxHeaderTypeDef structure to store the received header. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>data</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Array to store the received data. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>delay_ticks</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Maximum delay to wait if queue is empty (FreeRTOS ticks).</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>can_status_t Returns CAN_OK if a message was received, CAN_EMPTY if the queue was empty, CAN_ERR on failure or invalid ID. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
